{
  "stem": "26276.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Every day they could see-- the children could see with their own eyes, bringing in prisoners, loaded up on trucks, or any other vehicle, high up bodies.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the crematorium there was right-- actually maybe like 30 feet from their houses because the crematorium in Dachau was at the main gate, the main entrance, on the left hand side.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I can recall it just like-- this I can picture now.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the town must've stunk from the smell from the chimneys because the crematorium was burning there day and night.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had bodies laying outside by the piles of them to be burned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They couldn't catch up ever with the bodies.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when I was liberated, the first thing I thought to myself at that time would be, if I'm going to be able to, I'm going to run into those people to see what they had to say.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first question was, did you know what went inside across the street?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They made believe that they  didn't know a thing about it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made believe that they didn't know there was a camp in there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they saw prisoners marching in and out every single day by the thousands, and they denied this.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Two days later, after I was liberated, I got into Jerome's-- the soldier that I became friendly with-- I went into him, and I-- you know, I just ask him, I says, don't you-- don't you have a carabine?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because he was carrying a [? sight, ?] you know, a gun.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he says, yes, it's staying over there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, they had those short rifles, the outfit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I took that rifle, and I went in to see the German again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That lived outside the camp?",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
